handNote.seg:
Lapidary. Narrow letters. Alpha with slanting crossbar; the loops of beta are vertically spaced without touching each other; 
                           gamma and rho are sometimes embellished with an upward curling tail; theta with extended horizontal; 
                           the middle hastae of mu are angled to meet at the centre where they form a short vertical; upsilon is sometimes embellished with a short horizontal across the middle. 
                           Ligatures: nu-eta, tau-eta, omicron-upsilon, sigma-tau, pi-rho.
